Great food!
Edith served me and my party excellently! I had a very good time with a great server! Recommend!
Service and food was good. But the building was horrible. No AC. It was miserable there.

This was our first time at this location, and everything here was great. When we arrived the host said waiting time was an hour, but the most we waited was 15 minutes. They text you a link and you can track how many people are ahead of you.  Which I thought was marvelous.
The food was great!! So delicious!! We all came hungry and the food did not disappoint. The service was great. They were very attentive, changed our grills regularly and kept asking if we wanted anything else.
I would highly recommend this place especially if you are a meat lover!

comment.text:
I don't know how to feel about this location. I love Gen and have been to so many of their locations, but this one is such a hit and miss. We've come before on weekdays or weekends kind of early and are seated right away, good service, a little stuffy, food out on time, everything tastes good, no complaints.

We actually wanted to try U Grill and ended up at a different location than the one we wanted (the other U Grill on Foothill is not coming up anywhere for some reason) Music was blasting, I asked how long the wait was for 2 she snorted 2 hours so we bounced and decided to get Gen.

We walked into Gen and put our name down. The app is very off. There were a few groups ahead of us and our spot in line kept changing. It ended up taking 45 minutes until we got seated. They took us to the left side of the restaurant and someone took our drink and food order. The little apps and salads came out (such little portions btw) but no drinks. The waiter brought our water, but said the bartender was backed up. Other people were getting their drinks so not sure what the bartender was up to. Near the end of our meal we actually ended up getting our Soju and sodas.

Our food order never came out so we had to order with another waiter who noticed we didn't get our meats. He was so awesome! I think our waiter and this man  were the only servers in the whole restaurant, so I know their service was extremely slow that day because no enough servers were working. Not sure why they need 3 girls at the front check in though.

Food tasted good, drinks got me buzzed, so I was in a better mood :]

I feel bad, everyone is very nice here and the food has always tasted find to me. I think like all other business's they are understaffed. I'd recommend coming here early or during the week if you don't want to wait.

Came here with a friend on a hot Saturday afternoon, waited around 40 minutes to be seats, and was also told upfront that the a/c was out, which we were ok with. Upon seating, Edyth took our order promptly and ensured that our waters remained full. It helped a lot considering the heatwave going through the region at the time, and it made our stay a pleasant stay.

We had great and quick service with Edyth, she made sure all our orders were correct and was preemptive with making sure if we needed more orders or not. She was never too hard to reach or too long of a wait, and always came by to check up on us frequently. Overall, she made our stay very welcoming. I would come here again for the service.

As for the food, its typical Gen KBBQ, with a large selection and some new appetizers. I really do like the calamari fried bits, and would order those again.

So hot , no AC, terrible experience,
They tried to say it just broke but look in the reviews, I had to go outside to breathe multiple times.. and had to beg for water and sides multiple times. They say it's all you can eat but they make you wait so long time between "rounds" to get more meat. Food was tasteless and bland.. very over priced STAY AWAY!!

"That dinner was malicious" - a member of my party.

Overall Rating: 1.5/5

As far as Korean BBQ goes, this may be the worst experience I've had. All you can eat KBBQ doesn't warrant high quality meat, but some meats I couldn't be paid to bite through. Don't order the steak. This is the least full I have ever been after AYCE.

My party ordered:
-"Gen Premium" Steak - 0/5
- Beef bulgogi - 3/5
- Spicy Pork bulgogi - 3/5
- Brisket - 2/5

- Popcorn Chicken - 1/5
- Calamari - 1/5
- Yangyum Galbi - N/A
- Nook Gan Sal - 2/5

Let me start by saying this place is objectively not clean. I felt my shoes slipping on oil or grease. Please clean your floors. I wonder if that's why the lights are so dim in here. We get to the table and there are no tongs?

The side dishes were okay--definitely nothing to write home about. They gave us free rice at the start, which would've been nice had we not finished our rice, then requested more. This request was met with a 15-20 minute wait. This is somewhat unacceptable for a bowl of rice at this establishment, I would like to think. It appeared that there aren't that many dishes made by chefs, so one would think that having some rice going is pretty easy, but maybe the kitchen is understaffed or something. We also didn't get any sauce dishes. I feel these are pretty standard at kbbq. Pretty sure U-Grill down the street has sauce dishes or at least salt to dilute the blandness of some meats.

The meat that came was ok at best. Definitely lower end of meat quality. The best item out of those that we ordered was the spicy pork bulgogi, followed by the beef bulgogi. The marinades carry their flavor. All non-marinated items were pretty bland and chewy. The galbi never even came to our table.

Finally, the calamari was suspect at best and the popcorn chicken was oily and gross. Presentation was as shown in the pictures, which is to say, terrible.

Service - 1/5
Nathan must've been new, because better service should be expected of tenured waiters. On numerous occasions, we would order and then he would disappear without returning for over half an hour (just too long to be ok). I'm not sure how their service system works, but we received the wrong food on numerous occasions (3 i think). We never got the galbi despite waiting for ~40 total minutes for our second round. The calamari and popcorn chicken came at the very end of our meal after we had all but paid. A member of our party had to go to the bar to get a beer because they never brought it.

comment.text:
Gen has to be one of my sister's favorite restaurants. So we tend to come back often and have nothing but great experiences every time. Unfortunately today we had bad luck in which waiter was helping us. Didn't catch his name nor did I care to know, we were seated at 6:00pm and didn't get our first round of meat until 6:45 because he didn't seem to care about our party. Yet he was super attentive to the other tables around us.
It just seemed to be on purpose because we would try to make eye contact but it was as if he was avoiding us. Thankfully a lovely hostess (Vanessa) was there and helped us.

Had the worst experience here.  They were out of so many things took forever to bring our meat out   We didn't have the sauce on the table no scissors a to cut the meat.  Had to ask for everything we needed. Had to actually complain to the manager to even get meat on the table. Went to the restroom and it was atrocious with no supplies. I've never had such a horrible dining experience. They kept saying of the kitchens backed up. I would have preferred to wait longer for a table than to be sat and not taken care of. The manager didn't even give us a discount on the bill for such bad service. I won't be back this has definitely soured my opinion of this location. No pictures because we didn't have anything to take pictures of and by the time we did we were starving.

Waitress tipped herself out!!!!!!
The food and service was good until our waitress decided to create her own GENEROUS tip which is hugely inappropriate and fraudulent. Tried to make contact with the business several times but no one will answer the phone. Hugely disappointed as we are returning customers whilst feeling extremely taken advantage of. This business needs to be held accountable!
